        "timestamp": "2018-01-11 15:30:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIf we modify as suggested like below\n static Boolean isEdit = new Random().nextBoolean();\nThen if initially only if the Random function returns true then update function will be executed then it will be problem because first create has to be called.\n\nSo my modification is when create function executes immediately am making the value to true, so next time the update function will be executed. pls check once.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "6edc8e27ae997f7b6115e1677a5ca2df8e597841",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-11 21:13:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nAs is, the code will always hit the \n\nif (!isEdit) block\n\nand then the java process will exit, since it is intended to be used as a single dummy process with no purpose other than example code as Mike pointed out.\n\nEffectively the else statement is dead code, even if you change the flag in the if statement, the else will never be hit, that's what I'm trying to point out.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
